data.title: teleost fishes (Order Teleostei)
data.meta_description: The teleosts or Teleostei (Greek: teleios, 'complete' + osteon, 'bone') are by far the largest infraclass in the class Actinopterygii, the ray-finned fishes, and make up 96% of all extant species of fish. This diverse group arose in the Triassic period, and members are arranged in about 40 orders and 448 families. Over 26,000 species have been described.
